## Summary

Adds config-level Policy conformance checks for ingress/channel access posture:

```jsonc
{
  "ingress": {
    "session": {
      "requireDmScope": "per-channel-peer"
    },
    "channels": {
      "allowDmPolicies": ["pairing", "allowlist", "disabled"],
      "denyOpenGroups": true,
      "requireMentionInGroups": true
    }
  }
}
```

This stays in the config-conformance lane: it observes authored OpenClaw config, emits policy/doctor findings for drift, and does not add runtime enforcement.

The PR also extends the named `scopes.<scopeName>` overlay model from #85817 for channel-scoped ingress. Agent-scoped sections use `agentIds`; scoped ingress uses `channelIds` and supports the channel-attributable `ingress.channels.*` rules:

```jsonc
{
  "scopes": {
    "telegram-ingress": {
      "channelIds": ["telegram"],
      "ingress": {
        "channels": {
          "allowDmPolicies": ["pairing"],
          "denyOpenGroups": true,
          "requireMentionInGroups": true
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

Top-level `ingress.session.requireDmScope` remains global because `session.dmScope` is not channel-attributable evidence.

## Verification

- `pnpm exec oxfmt --check --threads=1 extensions/policy/src/doctor/register.ts extensions/policy/src/doctor/register.test.ts docs/cli/policy.md docs/plan/policy-agent-scoped-overlays.md docs/plugins/reference/policy.md`
- `pnpm exec oxlint extensions/policy/src/doctor/register.ts extensions/policy/src/doctor/register.test.ts`
- `pnpm docs:check-mdx docs/cli/policy.md docs/plugins/reference/policy.md docs/plan/policy-agent-scoped-overlays.md`
- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/policy/src/doctor/register.test.ts extensions/policy/src/cli.test.ts -- --reporter=verbose --testTimeout=30000` -> 2 files, 242 tests passed
- `git diff --check`

## Real behavior proof

Behavior addressed: Policy can now express direct-message scope, channel DM policy, open-group denial, group mention-gate, and channel-scoped ingress conformance requirements.

Real environment tested: WSL Ubuntu 24.04 checkout at `/root/src/openclaw-policy-ingress-channel`, rebased on updated #85817 and #85572 stack, using focused policy doctor and CLI tests.

Exact steps or command run after this patch: see Verification commands above.

Evidence after fix: focused tests cover failing ingress config, passing ingress config, disabled channel/account handling, inherited channel defaults, nested group mention overrides, Telegram root group inheritance for named accounts, and channel-scoped `channelIds` overlays.

Observed result after fix: the focused policy test suite passes with the new `channelIds` scoped ingress behavior and the docs/schema references point at `scopes.<scopeName>.ingress.channels.*`.

What was not tested: live channel runtime message delivery or enforcement; this PR intentionally adds Policy conformance/audit checks, not runtime enforcement.

